        <div class="prose intro">
            <p>Thirty-five days. Four countries. Twelve beds. One last great adventure before everything changes.</p>
            
            <p>This is not a vacation. It's a pilgrimage—through the light of Paris in winter, the impossible stillness of Venice before the crowds, the snow-capped silence of the Dolomites, the design temples of Milan, the thermal waters of a Swiss valley so remote it feels like the edge of the world. We end in London, a city we know, a language we share, a gentle landing before the flight home.</p>
            
            <p>We leave Mexico City on January 5th. We return on February 8th. In between: everything.</p>
